==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immense
<hw>Im*mense"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immensus</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>mensus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>metiri</ets> to measure: cf. F. <ets>immense</ets>. See
<er>Measure</er>.]</ety> <def>Immeasurable; unlimited. In commonest use:
Very great; vast; huge.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Immense</xex> the power⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Pope.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Immense</xex> and boundless ocean.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Daniel.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O Goodness infinite! Goodness <qex>immense</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Infinite; immeasurable; illimitable; unbounded;
unlimited; interminable; vast; prodigious; enormous; monstrous. See
<er>Enormous</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immensely</ent>⟦br⟧
